### <span id="10"></span>10.

   At that time in a certain district on the day of Uposatha the young
Bhikkhus, who had assembled first, thought: 'The Theras do not come
yet,' and went away. The Uposatha service was held after the right time.

   They told this thing to the Blessed One.

   'I prescribe, O Bhikkhus, that on the Uposatha day the Theras ought
to assemble first.'

