### <span id="11"></span>11.

   At that time there were at Râ*g*agaha several residences (of
Bhikkhus) within the same boundary. Now the Bhikkhus quarrelled: (some
of them said), 'The Uposatha shall be held in our residence;' (others
said), 'It shall be held in our residence.'

   They told this thing to the Blessed One.

   'There are, O Bhikkhus, several (Bhikkhu) residences within the same
boundary; now the Bhikkus quarrel: (some of them say), "The Uposatha
shall be held in our residence;" (others say), "It shall be held in our
residence." Let those Bhikkhus, O Bhikkhus, assemble in one place all of
them and hold Uposatha there, or let them assemble where <span
id="page_254">p. 254</span> the senior Bhikkhu dwells and hold Uposatha
there. But in no case is Uposatha to be held by an incomplete
congregation. He who holds it (in that way), commits a dukka*t*a
offence.'

