### <span id="28"></span>28.

   <span id="28:1"></span>1. At that time there assembled in a certain
residence (of Bhikkhus) at the day of Uposatha a number of resident
Bhikkhus, four or more. They did not know that there were other resident
Bhikkus absent. Intending to act according to Dhamma and Vinaya,
thinking themselves to be complete while (really) incomplete, they held
Uposatha and <span id="page_287">p. 287</span> recited the Pâtimokkha.
While they were reciting the Pâtimokkha, other resident Bhikkhus, a
greater number (than the first ones), arrived.

   They told this thing to the Blessed one.

    2. 'In case, O Bhikkhus, there assemble in a certain residence at
the day of Uposatha, &c. (§ 1); while they are reciting the Pâtimokkha,
other resident Bhikkhus, a greater number, arrive; let those Bhikkhus, O
Bhikkhus, recite the Pâtimokkha again; they who have recited it, are
free from guilt.

   <span id="28:3"></span>3. In case, O Bhikkhus, there assemble, &c.;
while they are reciting the Pâtimokkha, other resident Bhikkhus, exactly
the same number (as the first ones), arrive; in that case (the part of
the Pâtimokkha) that has been recited, has been correccly recited; let
those (who have arrived late), hear the rest; they who have recited it,
are free from guilt.

   'In case, O Bhikkhus, there assemble, &c.; while they are reciting
the Pâtimokkha, other resident Bhikkhus, a smaller number, arrive,
&c.<span id="page_287_fr_1"></span>[<sup><span
class="small">1</span></sup>](#page_287_note_1.md)

   <span id="28:4"></span>4. 'In case, O Bhikkhus, there assemble, &c.;
when they have just finished the recital of the Pâtimokkha, other
resident Bhikkhus, &c.<span id="page_287_fr_2"></span>[<sup><span
class="small">2</span></sup>](#page_287_note_2.md)

<span id="page_288">p. 288</span>

   <span id="28:5"></span>5. 'In case, O Bhikkhus, there assemble, &c.;
when they have just finished the recital of the Pâtimokkha, and the
assembly has not yet risen, other resident Bhikkhus, &c.<span
id="page_288_fr_1"></span>[<sup><span
class="small">1</span></sup>](#page_288_note_1.md)

   <span id="28:6"></span>6. 'In case, O Bhikkhus, there assemble, &c.;
when they have just finished the recital of the Pâtimokkha, and a part
of the assembly has risen, &c.<span
id="page_288_fr_1"></span>[<sup><span
class="small">1</span></sup>](#page_288_note_1.md)

   <span id="28:7"></span>7. 'In case, O Bhikkhus, there assemble, &c.;
when they have just finished the reciia\~ of the Pâtimokkha, and the
whole assembly has risen, &c.<span id="page_288_fr_1"></span>[<sup><span
class="small">1</span></sup>](#page_288_note_1.md)'

